race.comment: Tough. KISS MY ROCK (3) is a Victorian and as expected he turned the form around winning a CL1 over 1600m at Hobart. He settled back and belted home and on that effort he can come over the top again. SKY EAGLE (14) may be the best of the large Blacker contingent. Missed a lip here this grade/trip three back and has been within range over the distance at Hobart since. Always puts in and gets another chance. SNOW EAGLE (9) comes out of the same race won by MONTEZULU, and it was a much better run back to the mile. Maps well and has the blinkers applied for the first time. CORSA VELOCE (13) was threatening a win before a disappointing run stepping up to a middle distance. Come back to the mile 28 day freshen and has a key jockey switch with Byrne Burke replacing the 3kg apprentice. Has the rail and no surprise if she's back on track.
